UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2226
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION directing the University of Kentucky, the University of
2 Louisville, and Eastern Kentucky University to coordinate a search for actionable
3 solutions to physician shortages and to explore and expand health care opportunities in
4 medically underserved areas in collaboration with community, state agency, professional
5 associations, and other stakeholders, making an appropriation therefor, and declaring an
6 emergency.
7 WHEREAS, over 75 percent of physicians practice in urban areas in Kentucky,
8 leaving many counties with a shortage of physicians; and
9 WHEREAS, the United States Department of Health and Human Services has
10 designated 40 counties as health professional shortage areas for primary care providers;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, without local access to physicians, individuals in medically
13 underserved areas are often compelled to travel long distances to other counties for health
14 care, which may involve transportation and financial barriers and result in individuals
15 going without care; and
16 WHEREAS, regular primary care physician visits serve as the first line in
17 diagnosing illness and have been associated with a reduced number of hospitalizations
18 and emergency room department visits; and
19 WHEREAS, the Association of American Medical Colleges reports that 57 percent
20 of medical residents continued practicing medicine in their training state; and
21 WHEREAS, 38 percent of physicians practice medicine in the same state where
22 they completed undergraduate medical education, and the rate is higher for public
23 undergraduate medical school graduates, 46 percent; and
24 WHEREAS, according to the American Medical Association, the highest state
25 retention rates are for family medicine, 64.6 percent, psychiatry, 64.5 percent, and
26 pediatrics, 60 percent; and
27 WHEREAS, while some efforts have been made to increase medical residency
Page 1 of 4
